
Overview of noun purgation

The noun purgation has 3 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                    
1. catharsis, katharsis, purgation -- (purging the body by the use of a cathartic to stimulate evacuation of the bowels)
2. purification, purgation -- (a ceremonial cleansing from defilement or uncleanness by the performance of appropriate rites)
3. purge, purging, purgation -- (the act of clearing yourself (or another) from some stigma or charge)
